This paper focuses on the task of panoptic segmentation, which involves both semantic and instance segmentation. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also proposes a novel approach to modeling overlap relations among instances, which involves relational embedding and a differentiable module for overlap resolution. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves graph-based modeling and relational reasoning, which are relevant to the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques such as scene graph representation, which suggests that it may also belong to the computational linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category.
